<DOC><DOCNO> AP891220-0203 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-20-89 1914EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-WeatherpageWeather     12-20 0440</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Weatherpage Weather,0452</SECOND><HEAD>Winter Cold Reached Many Of The Gulf Of Mexico States</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Cold weather extended deep into the South and the Southwest onWednesday, with record lows in the nation's midsection, and heavysnow fell around Lake Erie.   Overnight temperatures reached 32 degrees or lower as far asmuch of North Carolina, south carolina, northern Georgia, northernAlabama, northern Mississippi, much of Louisiana, northerntwo-thirds of Texas, New Mexico, northeastern two-thirds ofArizona, east-central and north-central California, easterntwo-thirds of Oregon, and the eastern half of Washington state.   Below zero temperatures extended from across the upper half ofthe Plains, western Ohio, northern Maine, and the northeastern halfof Montana.   Wednesday's low for the Lower 48 states was 34 below zero atInternational Falls and Warroad, Minn. Unofficially, Embarrass, innortheastfern Minnesota, reached 37 degrees below zero.   Wednesday's record lows were 2 at Calico Rock, Ark.; 9 at HotSprings, Ark.; 4 at Paducah, Ky.; 12 below zero at Peoria, Ill.; 14below at Springfield, Ill.; and 11 below at Waukesha, Wis.   More than 100 low temperature records for the date have beenbroken or tied during the past week.   At noon, wind chill effects over South Dakota ranged from 20below zero in the south to 50 below zero in the north. Wind chillsreached 45 below zero in Upper Michigan.   Snow fell at midday over northeastern New York state, fromnorthwestern through east-central Pennsylvania, across northeasternOhio, over western Lower Michigan, from northwestern Illinoisacross southwestern Wisconsin, Iowa, southern Minnesota, SouthDakota, Nebraska, northwestern Wyoming and Montana.   In the snow belt of western New York state, where the moistureof Lake Erie contributes to ``lake effect'' snow, a highway wasclosed by 4-foot snow drifts between Holland and Sardina insouthern Erie County.   In northwestern Pennsylvania, also near Lake Erie, 12.4 inchesof snow fell overnight at Erie, 4 of that in one hour, and theairport was closed. That contributed to a total 30-inch snow cover.   A heavy snow warning in effect through Thursday was posted overnorthern Upper Michigan, and a winter storm watch in effect throughThursday was posted over western and northwest Lower Michigan.   A high wind warning was posted for this afternoon and tonightover east central and southeast wyoming. A wind chill warning fortonight was posted over north central through northeast wyoming.   Elsewhere, rain was scattered over the central FloridaPeninsula, and from southern Mississippi into southeasternLouisiana.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 p.m. EST ranged from 22degrees below zero at Roseglen, N.D., Warroad, Minn., andWilliston, N.D., to 84 at Homestead, Fla.</TEXT></DOC>